<h1>SimplyShaped Games</h1> <h2>(Welcome!)</h2>

<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>This is Simply Shaped Games' privacy policy for all of its published games, if you are interested in how I use your data throughout my games, please read carefully.<br>
If you have any questions, don't hesitate to contact me!</p>

<h3>Advertisement</h3>
<p>This paragraph explains in detail all advertisement related matters within Simply Shaped Games' games :</p>

<h4>Ad provider</h4>
<p>Simply Shaped Games uses Admob (by Google) as its main and only ad provider within its games.<br>
For more details about Admob, click on this link : https://admob.google.com/home/</p>

<h4>Why Ads?</h4>
<p>The sole reason why Simply Shaped Games uses ads in its games, is as its main revenue provider.<br>
Please understand that I need a revenue to support my family, and because all my games are free to play, I show ads to my players in order to generate a revenue.</p>

<h4>Why Ads?</h4>
<p>The sole reason why Simply Shaped Games uses ads in its games, is as its main revenue provider.<br>
Please understand that I need a revenue to support my family, and because all my games are free to play, I show ads to my players in order to generate a revenue.</p>

<h4>What type of ads?</h4>
<p>The sole reason why Simply Shaped Games uses ads in its games, is as its main revenue provider.</p>

<p>- Passive ads :<br>
(Passive ads are non voluntary ads that appear whilst the player is playing)<br>
- Interstitials</p>
<br>
<p>- Rewarded ads :<br>
(Rewarded ads are used to reward the player in exchange for them voluntarily watching a specific rewarded ad)<br>
- Rewarded interstitials<br>
- Rewarded videos</p>

<h4>Data Collection</h4>
<p>Simply Shaped Games does not directly collect any data from its players, nor does it use any personal data it could acquire from its ad provider (Admob).<br>
I simply look at how many and what type of ads have been showed and watched, and what revenue it has generated.</p>

